    "body": "Unfortunately not ready yet to open source.\r\n\r\nI'm recreating the simplest versions here:\r\n\r\nbuidler.config.js\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst defaultAccounts = require(\"./scripts/wallet-utils.js\");\r\nconst { usePlugin } = require('@nomiclabs/buidler/config');\r\nusePlugin(\"@nomiclabs/buidler-waffle\");\r\n\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  defaultNetwork: 'localhost',\r\n  networks: {\r\n    localhost: {\r\n      url: 'http://localhost:8545',\r\n    },\r\n    buidlerevm: {\r\n      accounts: defaultAccounts(),\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  solc: {\r\n    version : \"0.6.6\",\r\n    optimizer: {\r\n      enabled: true,\r\n      runs: 200\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\ndefaultAccounts is just and HD Wallet.\r\n\r\ntest\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst { time } = require('@openzeppelin/test-helpers');\r\n\r\nconst { expect } = require(\"chai\");\r\n\r\ndescribe(\"timetest\", function() {\r\n\r\n  it('time fail', async () => {\r\n    await time.increase(10); // 10 seconds increase.\r\n  });\r\n\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat was interesting. I noticed strange behaviour. When I was running a stand-alone node, running tests using the in-process EVM, the 'increaseTime' call would send it to the stand-alone node, NOT the in-process EVM.\r\n\r\nSo not sure if it's config file related or whether increaseTime has a default RPC it's trying to connect to? Maybe it's due to my config?",
