    "body": "Hey @simondlr,\r\n\r\nThanks for posting more info about your problem.\r\n\r\nThis is some really unexpected behavior of `@openzeppelin/test-helpers`. It tries to use a globally available instance of `web3`. If it doesn't find one, it initializes a provider pointing to `localhost:8545`. The error you are getting is that `web3` gets no response, as there's no node running on that port.\r\n\r\nYou can use `@openzeppelin/test-helpers` with an in-process Buidler EVM by installing `@nomiclabs/buidler-web3` and `web3`, and adding `usePlugin(\"@nomiclabs/buidler-web3\");` to your config.\r\n\r\nLet me know if this worked.",
