    "body": "@coostendorp Hey, I'm very grateful for your comment, what a hint!\r\n\r\nI'm currently learning about smart contract development in Ethereum, and until now I've been using `JavaScript + Truffle + Web3 + Jest + OZ Test Environment + OZ Test Helpers`.\r\nA few days ago I switched to `TypeScript (TypeChain) + Buidler + Ethers.js + Waffle (mocha/chain)` just for giving it a try, and I wasn't sure how I about manipulating the blocks/time on my tests. The learning curve with this new stack is quite step and I didn't want to end up installing all the Truffle-Web3-Ganache plugins for Buidler.\r\nToday I had an aha moment about porting the `time` OZ Test Helper, so I inspected it and saw the `evm` manipulation... but of course using Web3 and for Ganache-cli. Nonetheless as soon as I saw your comment I connected the dots, checked the Budler EVM documentation, and ported the library (locally). It works!\r\nTo be honest I'm very looking forward for Waffle officially supporting Jest, and OZ supporting ethers.js.\r\n\r\nThanks\r\n\r\n[Time OZ Test Helpers](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-test-helpers/blob/master/src/time.js)",
