    "body": "> In case it helps anyone, I ended up doing the following (using ethers5, waffle, buidler):\r\n> \r\n> ```\r\n> ...\r\n> ethers.provider.send(\"evm_mine\")      // mine the next block\r\n> ```\r\n\r\nWhile coding in typescript, I need to use this\r\n```typescript\r\nawait (provider as any).send('evm_mine');\r\n```\r\nto avoid the following error. \r\n\r\n```\r\nError in plugin solidity-coverage: TSError: ⨯ Unable to compile TypeScript:\r\ntest/MyTest.ts:266:22 - error TS2554: Expected 2 arguments, but got 1.\r\n\r\n266       await provider.send('evm_mine');\r\n                         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n\r\n  node_modules/@ethersproject/providers/lib/web3-provider.d.ts:26:26\r\n    26     send(method: string, params: Array<any>): Promise<any>;\r\n                                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    An argument for 'params' was not provided.\r\n```",
